-- Ukraine Needs $150 Million for Airport Renovation, Interfax Says
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2012-11-23T10:54:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-23/ukraine-needs-150-million-for-airport-renovation-interfax-says.html
Ukraine will need about $150 million
of investment to complete the renovation Boryspil, the country’s
main international airport, Interfax-Ukraine newswire reported,
citing Dmytro Demydovych, deputy infrastructure minister.  The ministry may offer a concession to operate the airport,
Interfax cited Demydovych as saying. Boryspil’s outstanding debt
is about $700 million, Demydovych told the newswire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
